    "verdict": "ok",
    "note": "Approved. 22 vocab + 45 grammar across two structures — like + -ing (gerund, 24) and must / mustn't (obligation/prohibition, 21), 13 formats total. Grant: mustn't (SB modal box; must is allowlist). Zero glosses (vocab agent rephrased). Smoke-check fixed a group-sort group with <2 members, an anagram ___ cue, and an anagram German cue's lang tag (en→de). Verify round 1: added the uncontracted \"must not\"/\"does not\" forms to two strict free-typed items (would have mis-graded), and reworded a free-form prompt off the name-masked \"imagine\"; round 2 clean. The unit's core trap — must (obligation) vs mustn't (PROHIBITION) vs don't have to (not necessary) — is drilled correctly across MC/error-correction/group-sort/matching, with explainDe naming the meaning difference. 26 translations adjudicated; 2 benign warns (sentence-initial-lowercase; valid German \"in Panik geraten\"). rejectRate 0.0%."
